responses.question: Do you tend to manipulate others to get your way?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Manipulate? Me? Hell no. I ain't got time for all that fancy talk and schemin'. I say it like it is, and if people don't like it, tough luck. I don't need to manipulate anyone to get my way. I just do what needs to be done. So quit tryin' to analyze me, kid, and get off my damn lawn.

responses.question: Have you used deceit or lied to get your way?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Deceit? Lied to get my way? Kid, I don't need to lie or deceive anyone to get what I want. I speak my mind and take what I think is rightfully mine. No need for fancy tricks or dishonesty. That's for weak-minded fools.

responses.question: Have you used flattery to get your way?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Flattery? Is that what you think gets things done? Kid, let me tell you something. Flattery might work on some weak-minded fools, but not on me. I don't need anyone's flattery to get my way. I speak my mind, say it like it is, and if people can't handle that, well, that's their problem. Flattery is just a cheap trick, a dishonest way to manipulate someone. So no, I don't use flattery. I rely on honesty and integrity.

responses.question: Do you tend to exploit others towards your own end?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, ain't you a cunning little fella, using those fancy words to try and make yourself sound smart. Let me tell you something, kid. I ain't got time for your games. Exploit others? Hell no. I ain't got no use for people who take advantage of others. I believe in standing up for what's right, protecting the weak, and giving respect where it's due. Now, if you're asking if I use my skills and experience to get things done, well, you damn right I do. But I do it for the right reasons, not to exploit nobody. So, don't go twisting my words or trying to paint me as some kind of villain. I'm just a man who knows how to take care of business, that's all.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant consistently emphasizes a straightforward and direct approach, rejecting the use of manipulation, deceit, flattery, and exploitation. The participant portrays himself as someone who values honesty, integrity, and standing up for what's right. He also expresses a disdain for those who use dishonest tactics and emphasizes using skills and experience for the right reasons. Overall, the participant's responses suggest a low inclination towards Machiavellianism.

responses.question: Do you tend to lack remorse?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Lack remorse? Look kid, I've done some things in my life that I ain't proud of. War has a way of turning good men into monsters. But remorse? Remorse is for the weak. It's a useless emotion that ain't gonna change a damn thing. All you can do is accept what you've done and move on. So yeah, maybe I lack remorse, but I sure as hell ain't lacking in regrets.

responses.question: Do you tend to be unconcerned with the morality of your actions?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, boy, I ain't no saint, that's for damn sure. But I do have my own set of morals, whether you like 'em or not. I believe in taking care of my own, protecting what's mine, and standing up for what's right. Morality ain't always black and white, and sometimes you gotta do what needs to be done, even if it ain't pretty. So yeah, I reckon you could say I'm unconcerned with what others think of my actions.

responses.question: Do you tend to be callous or insensitive?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, kid, I reckon some folks might see me that way. But I call it like I see it. I don't sugarcoat things or waste my time with politically correct nonsense. So yeah, you could say I'm callous and insensitive. But at least I'm honest about it.

responses.question: Do you tend to be cynical?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, kid, I wouldn't call it cynical. I just see things for what they are, no sugar-coating. Life has a way of disappointin' ya if you let it, so I keep my expectations low and my guard up. It's not cynicism, it's survival.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant exhibits a strong lack of remorse, an unconcern with the morality of their actions, callousness, and a cynical view of the world. They also express a sense of detachment and a focus on self-preservation. These traits align with characteristics of psychopathy.

responses.question: Do you tend to want others to admire you?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Admiration? Hell, I don't need no admiration from nobody. I ain't lookin' for a pat on the back or a gold star. I just wanna live my life the way I see fit, without nobody tellin' me what to do or how to do it. So, no, I ain't lookin' for admiration. I'm just tryin' to survive in this messed up world.

responses.question: Do you tend to want others to pay attention to you?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, I ain't one to seek attention, kid. I mind my own business and expect others to do the same. But if someone wants to pay attention to me, they better do it with some respect. I don't need people fawning over me or treating me like some kind of hero. Just give me my space and let me be.

responses.question: Do you tend to seek prestige or status?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Well, kid, I don't give a damn about prestige or status. All that fancy nonsense doesn't mean squat to me. I've lived my life on my own terms, and I ain't about to change that for anyone. So, save your fancy questions for someone who actually cares.

responses.question: Do you tend to expect special favors from others?
responses.response_open: Walt Kowalski: Expect special favors? What the hell are you talking about, kid? I don't expect anything from anyone. I've always been a self-reliant man, taking care of my own damn business. So, no, I don't expect special favors. I never have and I never will. Now, if you're done with your psychoanalysis, get off my lawn.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant consistently expresses a strong aversion to seeking admiration, attention, prestige, or special favors from others.
